          What is the difference between Yam porridge and yam pottage?
          The two terms are used to describe meals. Porridge, in its classical meaning, mainly refers to the original English oatmeal or other porridges made of grains. Pottage is widely used in Nigeria and many other African countries, mainly as a synonym to porridge. Both porridge and pottage in Nigeria mean the main dish.26 Feb 2018

          Is Yam porridge good for weight loss?
          With just 157 calories in a cup, yams can be an excellent food when you're trying to lose weight. In addition, the natural fiber in yams helps to slow down the rate your body processes sugar, keeping you from being hungry between meals.
